Description: Two-character abbreviation for the domain, which must be TT.
Short name of the Repro Stage used for programming and sorting. Maximum 8 characters.
The name of the Repro Stage.

Variable Label: Rule for Start of Repro Stage
Description: Expresses the rule for beginning the Repro Stage.

Variable Label: Rule for End of Repro Stage
Description: Expresses the rule for ending the Repro Stage. Either TTENRL or TTDUR must be present for each Repro Stage.
Planned Duration of Repro Stage. Used when the rule for ending the Repro Stage is applied after a fixed duration.
